This peptide is found in different species of arenavirus family.  Phenylalanine at position 375 seems to be Lassa virus-specific for the binding of monoclonal antibody 9-7.9.   Lassa-specific F to Y change at position 375 resulted in almost total loss of binding by MAb 9-7.9 without loss of 33.6 binding.

This epitope is the posttranslationally modified form of LCMV GP92-101 in which the Asparagine at position 95 is converted to Aspartic Acid.  It is copresented with the genetically encoded form (CSANNSHHYI) at the surface of LCMV-infected H-2b cells.

The genetically encoded sequence for this subdominant epitope, is N-glycosylated in the mature glycoprotein at N95 residue in the glycosylation motif NX(S/T). An artificial peptide, with the sequence CSADNSHHYI  as a N95D deaminated analog is used (as in vivo the de-N-glycosylation by cytoplasmic N-glycanases also deaminates residue N95 to a D residue in its place) to analyze the effect of deglycosylation/deamidation on MHC binding and CTL recognition.

The genetically encoded sequence for this subdominant epitope, is N-glycosylated in the mature glycoprotein at N95 residue in the glycosylation motif NX(S/T). An artificial peptide with GlcNac N-glycosylation is used to analyze the effect of glycosylation on MHC binding and CTL recognition.

An internal source ID is assigned, because the sequence provided in the reference differs from those found by BLAST at residue L at position 8. This is due to the fact that this epitope was found in a variant virus selected with T cells with specificity for the natural peptide NP396-404, FQPQNGQFI.
The epitope sequence was found in the cited reference van der Most et al., J Virol. 1997 Jul;71(7):5110-4 [PMID: 9188577].

The GP33-43 H-2Db-restricted epitope of the LCMV glycoprotein was previously delineated by Gairin JE et al J Virol 1995;69:2297-2305.  GP35-43 represents a N terminal truncation of GP33-43 of LCMV glycoprotein made to determine the minimal optimal epitope.

The genetically encoded sequence is N-glycosylated in the mature glycoprotein 2 at N396 residue in the glycosylation motif NX(S/T). An artificial peptide, with the sequence WLVTDGSYL  as a N396D deaminated analog is used (as in vivo the de-N-glycosylation by cytoplasmic N-glycanases also deaminates residue N396 to a D residue in its place) to analyze the effect of deglycosylation/deamidation on MHC binding and CTL recognition.

This is a variant from the known subdominant LCMV epitope NP205-212, found in an escape mutant virus. The escape mutant origin of the epitope requires an IEDB ID.
The epitope sequence was previously described in Dow et al., J Virol: 82(11734) 2008 [PMID:18829752].
